<div class="center jumbotron" style="height: 457px">
<h3>Welcome to Course Feedback System</h3>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="tab">
      <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, 'forum')" id="defaultOpen">Forum</button>
      <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, 'course_eval')">Course-Eval</button>
      <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, 'suggestion')">Suggestion</button>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div id="forum" class="tabcontent">
        <p style="margin-top: 4%;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px"> If you have want to discuss any dilemmas before selecting a course, the Forum

          will help you enter a channel of a specific course and post the questions. The

          users of the channel will be the students who had studied the course in previous

          semesters. They can give reply to your post, the like and dislike feature on their replies

          can help you make a decision.</p>
        <div class="button">
          <%= link_to "Forum", show_course_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-primary" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="course_eval" class="tabcontent">
        <p style="margin-top: 4%;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px"> In this approach, you can get a feedback for a particular course you would

          like to enroll in. The feedback is an average result of answers to frequently asked

          questions before selecting a course. The feedback answers are provided by the students

          who have already completed the course.</p>
        <div style="display: inline-flex; margin-top: 18%;margin-left: 52%">
          <div id="giveFeedback">
            <%= link_to "Give Feedback", course_eval_givefeedback_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-primary" %>
          </div>
          <div id="getFeedback">
            <%= link_to "Get Feedback", course_eval_getfeedback_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-primary" %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="suggestion" class="tabcontent">
        <p style="margin-top: 4%;font-weight: bold;font-size: 15px"> This approach will suggest you courses, as per the choices you select in the

          filters search. The filter search includes choices as your specific expectation from course

          like languages/ tools used, number of projects included. etc</p>
        <div class="button">
          <%= link_to "Suggestion", suggestion_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-primary" %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
<style>
  .button{
    margin-top: 20%;
    margin-left: 77%;
  }
  #giveFeedback{

  }
  #getFeedback{
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  #forum{
    background-image: url("/assets/forum.jpg");
    background-size: cover;


  }
  #course_eval{
    background-image: url("/assets/course_eval.jpg");
    background-size: cover;
  }
  #suggestion{
    background-image: url("/assets/suggestion.jpg");
    background-size: cover;
  }
  /* Style the tab */
  div.tab {
    float: left;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    background-color: #f1f1f1;
    width: 15%;
    height: 97%;
  }

  /* Style the buttons inside the tab */
  div.tab button {
    display: block;
    background-color: inherit;
    color: black;
    padding: 49.1px 30px;
    width: 100%;
    border: none;
    outline: none;
    text-align: left;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: 0.3s;
    font-weight: bold;

  }

  /* Change background color of buttons on hover */
  div.tab button:hover {
    background-color: #ddd;
  }

  /* Create an active/current "tab button" class */
  div.tab button.active {
    background-color: #ccc;
  }

  /* Style the tab content */
  .tabcontent {
    float: left;
    padding: 0px 12px;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    width: 85%;
    border-left: none;
    height: 355px;
  }

  .tabcontent {
    -webkit-animation: fadeEffect 1s;
    animation: fadeEffect 1s; /* Fading effect takes 1 second */
  }

  @-webkit-keyframes fadeEffect {
    from {opacity: 0;}
    to {opacity: 1;}
  }

  @keyframes fadeEffect {
    from {opacity: 0;}
    to {opacity: 1;}
  }

</style>
<script>
  // Get the element with id="defaultOpen" and click on it
  document.getElementById("defaultOpen").click();

  function openCity(evt, cityName) {
    // Declare all variables
    var i, tabcontent, tablinks;

    // Get all elements with class="tabcontent" and hide them
    tabcontent = document.getElementsByClassName("tabcontent");
    for (i = 0; i < tabcontent.length; i++) {
      tabcontent[i].style.display = "none";
    }

    // Get all elements with class="tablinks" and remove the class "active"
    tablinks = document.getElementsByClassName("tablinks");
    for (i = 0; i < tablinks.length; i++) {
      tablinks[i].className = tablinks[i].className.replace(" active", "");
    }

    // Show the current tab, and add an "active" class to the button that opened the tab
    document.getElementById(cityName).style.display = "block";
    evt.currentTarget.className += " active";
  }
</script>